snippet.textDisplay:
For the Children, Jimmy !

Please Share With as Many Young Children as You Can! I'm a self-quarantined teacher and songwriter who's getting emails from FRANTIC MOM'S trying to keep their little ones busy at home!I keep trying to "inform" them, that this VIRUS does NOT want to live in their dirty, germ-filled, cupboards nor kitchen counters, It wants to come in on the coat tails of your VISITORS' and friend' s CLOTHING and move in to your LUNGS! God Bless You All During this Crisis We are all Praying for You!THIS TO EMPOWER those little ones who are scared! ! (I say..."The Devil be Gone With The Wind".It's like the "Big Bad Wolf, has escaped!)Please Share With as Many Young Children as You Can! (or write me if you are a musician)


"it" fly's through the air, with the greatest of ease,"
This Devilish Dragon, on his flying trapeze!
He's big and his bad, but he does not scare me,
God will be watching the coughs and the sneeze!

This invisible Devil, like leaves in a breeze,
Will float by your window and out through the trees,
He wants to find us, through the air that we breathe,
But he'll Soon be Gone With the Wind

Like the " sun in the morning, peeped over the hill,"
Like the rain comes to wash away tears that we spill,
We will be out there playing , with the love that God sends,
And the Devil, Be Gone With the Wind.

Yes, I wanted to break into a new chorus on "The Devil being gone with the wind" but it just started to become a totally different song,that being such a strong musical phrase - and a bit to emotional for "The Little Ones.?"

Melody, admittedly, was derived (ok, slightly "borrowed' apparently, subconsciously, not purposely) from each of the songs "Mocking Bird Hill", and "The Man on the Flying Trapeze! (UK) copyrights-now public domain; both written four years after the INFLUENZA of 1918! 100 years later, it's back, apparently with mutations to come ? I just wanted to do "something" to Empower the Children! ( And the Flying Trapeze is already en-grained in their parents' heads?!) LyndaFayeSmusic@@t
